<br>
This is really the way it works.  I've never played a wizard, but I have a 52 druid and 52 bard so I know how swarm and quad kiting work.<br>
<br>
Druid/Wizard soloing.  huges amounts of exp followed by long down time.<br>
<br>
Bard soloing.  slow and steading exp, no down time, and in many cases, arthritus(sp?).<br>
<br>
It all comes out about the same. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/recursion0/Aslaan.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=recursion0>Recursion0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/24/02 4:24:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=105>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard kiting</span><hr size=1> doh, can't edit my post so I'll just add this.<br>
