<br>
While we all OOC'd our &quot;Yo dude back off/please dont train/please watch where you are going&quot; he actually got worse.  Even the lower level players just there for the goranga groups were getting killed.  It became a fight for our lives as he agroed the entire toiler area AND much of the sourrounding areas then brought them all back to the corner behind the hill and let em go at eachother.  Coming back over the hill every so often to agro any new pops right out from under us, training us if we were solo'ing or kiting anything that he wanted.<br>
<br>
On the one hand it was an impressive feat.<br>
On the other hand he was monopolizing 1/4 of an entire ZONE and training/killing players on purpose.<br>
<br>
I and the other wizards started talking.  It seems he had done this before and always left before a /report /petition brought anyone and everyone was sick of it (and him).  Well the druid and all us wizzies started gathering trap mobs.  Each of us pulled a train at the same time you would not believe and ran straight to the tip of the hill and we absconded at the last second settig a wall of mobs who would stick there for a few minutes.  It was breathtaking to see and amazing that it worked.<br>
<br>
We juuuust ran back in time to see him re-grouping his toilers and shoot over the hill.  His death was almost instant and the entire zone cheered when he started cussing. Now I am fully aware that I broke all sorts of rules, and that sony could get on me for what we did but I honestly feel this was warrented.<br>
<br>
A good bard, who knows his stuff is an awesome player and an increadible grouping partner, a bad bard or inconsiderate bard can ruin a camp through not undrestanding what happens in his wake.  An asshole Bard who is training EVERYONE on purpose can almost shut down a small zone entirely and cause a lot of deaths.  I feel no guilt at all.<br>
<br>
Oh and the next time a bard monopolizes the birds (as is clearly NOT supposed to be done)?  I suppose you COULD Just shoot your atols in the middle of the mobs and grab 4, start nuking and ignore him.   If everyone did that at the same time he'd get the message and 0 mobs to boot.  I suppose... heh Im not SAYING you SHOULD.... just that you could if you all acted together.<br>
